AN ARMED robber has been jailed for seven years after targeting a woman worker in a bookmaker's in a gun raid. Seven years for armed raid at bookies AN ARMED robber has been jailed for seven years after targeting a woman worker in a bookmaker's in a gun raid.Stephen Flynn, 43, went into the branch of William Hill's in Paisley Road West, Glasgow, with a handgun and demanded that the employee open cash registers and put money from a coin dispenser in a bag.Flynn robbed his victim, Karen Wishart, of &pound;107 during the raid on May 12 this year. 